### Key AST Types (from `src/syntax/ast.kk`)

**`hica-type`** ŌĆö the type system:
```koka
TInt | TFloat | TBool | TString | TChar | TUnit
TTuple( elems : list<hica-type> )
TList( elem : hica-type )
TMaybe( elem : hica-type )
TResult( ok-type : hica-type, err-type : hica-type )
TFun( params : list<hica-type>, result : hica-type )
TStruct( name : string )
TEnum( name : string )
TVar( name : string )   // type variable (unification)
```

**`binop`** ŌĆö note: Koka syntax is `pub type binop`, NOT `enum binop`:
```koka
pub type binop
  Add | Sub | Mul | Div | Mod
  Eq | Neq | Lt | Gt | Le | Ge
  And | Or | In
```

**`node`** ŌĆö every expression is a `node`:
```koka
struct node
  span : span             // source location for errors
  expr : expr
  typ  : maybe<hica-type> // filled in by checker
```

**`expr`** ŌĆö the expression enum (key variants):
```koka
Literal( lit : literal )
Var( name : string )
Let( name, type-ann, init : node, body : node )
VarDecl( name, type-ann, init : node, body : node )
Assign( name, value : node )
Fun( params : list<string>, body : node )
Call( callee : node, args : list<node> )
Binary( op : binop, lhs : node, rhs : node )
Unary( op : unop, operand : node )
If( cond, then-expr, else-expr : node )
Block( stmts : list<node> )
Match( scrutinee : node, arms : list<match-arm> )
ForIn( name, start, end, body : node )
ForEach( name, collection, body : node )
While( condition, body : node )
Loop( body : node ) | Break | Continue
Repeat( count, body : node )
StringInterp( parts : list<node> )
Tuple( elems : list<node> )
TupleIndex( tuple : node, index : int )
EList( elems : list<node> )
MapLit( entries : list<(node, node)> )
ListIndex( list, index : node )
ListSlice( list, slice-start, slice-end : maybe<node> )
LetTuple( names, init, body : node )
StructLit( struct-name, fields : list<(string, node)> )
StructUpdate( struct-name, base : node, fields : list<(string, node)>, def-fields : list<string> )
FieldAccess( obj : node, field-name : string )
ESome( value ) | ENone | EOk( value ) | EErr( value )
EConstructor( ctor-name, ctor-args : list<node> )
ETry( inner : node )   // ? operator
```

**`pattern`** ŌĆö match arm patterns:
```koka
PWild | PVar( name ) | PLit( lit )
PSome( inner ) | PNone | POk( inner ) | PErr( inner )
PTuple( elems : list<pattern> )
POr( alts : list<pattern> )
PConstructor( ctor-name, ctor-args : list<pattern> )
PStruct( struct-name, field-pats : list<(string, pattern)>, def-fields )
PList( elems : list<pattern>, rest : maybe<pattern> )
PRange( lo : int, hi : int )
PBits( msk : int, val_ : int )
```

**`match-arm`**:
```koka
struct match-arm
  pattern : pattern
  guard   : maybe<node>
  body    : node
```

